The paper deals with the initialization of convolutional neural networks for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses unsupervised and self-supervised pre-training methods, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. The use of initialization to avoid vanishing or exploding gradients is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE), and the paper's focus on image classification and object detection tasks suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
